properties.description: Family: Rosaceae Squamish habitat: Estuary edge of floodplain forest Squamish location: East Delta Swan Trail by Crescent Slough
typical example, salmonberries in Estuary are beginning to bloom, end of March 2019

Ceroplastes is the first possibility iNaturalist suggests. Host looks to be Rubus spectabilis, it's hard to be sure until this shrub leafs out. Salmonberry is common in this area but there weren't others in close proximity. Adjacent shrubs did not have these and I haven't seen them elsewhere so far. Moist, mixed forest of native vegetation. There are almost no introduced species here, however it's alongside a mountain bike trail.
